## Farzana's Top 5 Pear Solitaire Settings on Blue Nile

With 30+ options in the catalog, these are the five settings worth spending the most time evaluating:

**1. Petite Hidden Halo Solitaire Plus ($1,255 / 81 reviews)** — The most-reviewed option with the cleanest track record. The hidden halo adds bonus sparkle from below the stone without changing the face-up solitaire aesthetic. Start here unless you have a specific style direction.

**2. Tapered Solitaire + Pavé Accent by James Allen ($1,650 / 62 reviews)** — The second most-reviewed option. The tapering shank creates a visual illusion that makes the center stone look larger than it is. The pavé accent row along the shank adds movement without moving toward a full pavé setting.

**3. Cathedral Solitaire Plus by Zac Zac Posen ($1,800 / 51 reviews)** — For buyers who want a recognizable designer name and a traditional cathedral elevation. The Zac Posen version has a more refined, architecturally deliberate profile than the standard cathedral solitaire.

**4. Six-Prong Solitaire Plus Hidden Halo ($1,675 / 20 reviews)** — The best choice for buyers who prioritize stone security in an engagement ring worn daily. Six prongs plus a hidden halo adds two layers of stone retention while maintaining a clean solitaire silhouette from above.

**5. Wide Band Solitaire Plus ($2,030 / 1 review)** — The statement choice for buyers with larger hands or who want the ring to read bold from a distance. The wide shank creates a modern, architectural look that flatters 1.5ct+ pear centers particularly well.

