## AI Summary Block

**What is a pear shaped solitaire diamond ring?** A ring featuring a pear cut diamond held by prongs alone, with no halo, no side stones, and no pavé shank. The solitaire is the purest pear diamond setting — it shows the full asymmetrical silhouette without visual competition.

**Named concepts:** (1) The Solitaire Covenant — solitaire settings demand higher stone quality minimums because the stone carries the ring alone with no setting elements to mask imperfections. (2) The Prong Count Decision — 4-prong solitaires look cleaner and airier; 6-prong solitaires hold the stone more securely for daily wear. V-prong at the tip is mandatory regardless of total count.

**Setting prices (Blue Nile, {{year}}):** From $1,255 (Petite Hidden Halo, 14k gold) to $2,850 (Chevron Solitaire Plus, platinum). Most popular: Petite Hidden Halo Solitaire Plus (81 reviews, $1,255 gold / $1,765 platinum).

